### High-Probability Tricky MCQ Targets

**1.** The **ozone layer** is in the stratosphere — not the mesosphere or troposphere.

**2.** The **coldest layer** of the atmosphere is the **mesosphere** (~−90°C at mesopause) — NOT the stratosphere.

**3.** **Noctilucent clouds** form in the mesosphere (~80 km); **nacreous/mother-of-pearl clouds** form in the stratosphere.

**4.** The tropopause is **higher at the equator** (~16–18 km) and **lower at the poles** (~8 km) — temperature inversion starts here.

**5.** **97.5% of water is saline**; of freshwater, the largest store is **glaciers and ice caps** (~69%), NOT rivers or lakes.

**6.** The **lithosphere includes upper mantle + crust**, not just crust. Plate tectonics happens because the lithosphere floats on the **asthenosphere**.

**7.** The Earth's magnetic field is generated by the **liquid outer core**, not the solid inner core.

**8.** **SIAL** (lighter, continental crust) floats on **SIMA** (heavier, oceanic crust) — this is why continents don't subduct easily.

**9.** Life exists in the biosphere up to ~10 km altitude and down to ~11 km ocean depth — so the biosphere **penetrates all other spheres**.

**10.** Water has **maximum density at 4°C** (not 0°C) — this is why lakes freeze from the top, protecting aquatic life.

